<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-82-0899 </DOCNO><TEXT>In recent years substantial action has been taken within the oil refiningindustry to reduce their own inhouse energy consumption and hence cost.However, much of this has been achieved by technical change. The bulkof this paper is concerned with the somewhat less easy but far more cost-effectivearea of managing energy, and let me say from the outset that even wheresophisticated technical solutions are adopted, they need to be properlymanaged if full benefits are to be obtained. The paper is backed up withpertinent examples and suggests that the remaining potential for achievementof operational energy usage reduction in the oil refining industry issignificant.</TEXT></DOC>